        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 2: Distribution of Chaetostoma formosae sp. nov. Square = type locality; Circles = remaining localities. One symbol may represent either more than one locality or lot of specimens. Dashed areas represent the 3000 masl contour, dotted areas represent the 1000 masl contour. Southernmost symbol with a question mark represents an erroneous record for Leticia, Amazonas, Colombia. Base map provided by John D. Lynch." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4901064/files/figure.png" .

